Former Big Brother Naija reality television star, Saskay, has reacted to the death of Nollywood actress, Ada Ameh. Saskay described Ameh’s death as ‘sad’, adding that she met her once on set and she was so sweet. DAILY POST reports that ‘The Johnsons’ star, collapsed and died around 11 pm on Sunday. Recall that Ada Ameh had, on June 15, opened up on her battle with mental health. She had said the issue was gradually taking her life, but she believes that she will not die and will get over it. Reacting to the sad news, Saskay, in a tweet via her Twitter handle, on Monday morning, wrote: “I met this woman once on set and she was so sweet like she had known me before. “All I could think of was the grief she was experiencing, cause I had seen several videos where she spoke about her mental health. This is really sad. Rest well Ada Ameh.”